<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="273" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1494,2026]" pageId="7" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1893,1918]" pageId="7" pageNumber="273">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is extremely similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Dworakowska" authorityName="Dworakowska" box="[772,1087,1893,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hepneriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="joannae">
<emphasis box="[772,896,1894,1917]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="273">H. joannae</emphasis>
(Dworakowska)
</taxonomicName>
, but the lamellar process of the style is shorter with the ventral ridge indistinct, the aedeagal shaft is broader and the subapical processes are distinctly curved laterad.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1011,2001,2026]" pageId="7" pageNumber="273" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1494,2026]" box="[199,1011,2001,2026]" pageId="7" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,2001,2026]" pageId="7" pageNumber="273">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named after its 
<typeStatus box="[731,779,2002,2026]" pageId="7" pageNumber="273">type</typeStatus>
locality “Menglun”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
